</div> 
<p><strong>Reduvia</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Daggers" href="/Daggers" target="">Dagger</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Reduvia</strong>&nbsp;scales with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength" target="">Strength</a>, <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dexterity" href="/Dexterity" target="">Dexterity</a>, and&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Arcane" href="/Arcane">Arcane</a>. It is one of the first weapons the player can acquire that scales with Arcane and is exceptional at inflicting Blood Loss on targets.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Jagged dagger with a distinctive curled blade.<br>Carried by the noble servants of the Lord of Blood.</em></p> 
 <p><em>This dagger rips the flesh as it enters, inflicting blood loss with sickening efficacy. A proud testament to the success of its vicious design, this weapon is perpetually coated in blood.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Reduvia in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Reduvia weapon can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Dropped by <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Bloody Finger Nerijus" href="/Bloody+Finger+Nerijus">Bloody Finger Nerijus</a>. [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=1217&amp;lat=-186.32&amp;lng=110.05&amp;zoom=8" href="/Interactive+Map?id=1217&amp;lat=-186.32&amp;lng=110.05&amp;zoom=8">Map Link</a>]</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Reduvia Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Reduvia Blood Blade" href="/Reduvia+Blood+Blade">Reduvia Blood Blade</a></li> 
 <li>Cannot be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a>.</li> 
 <li><strong>U</strong>pgraded using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones">Somber Smithing Stones</a>.</li> 
 <li>The small wave of blood, launched by the weapon's skill, flies a relatively short distance, but can still be used while staying outside the melee attack range of most enemies.</li> 
 <li>The weapon's skill, <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Reduvia Blood Blade" href="/Reduvia+Blood+Blade">Reduvia Blood Blade</a>, inflicts more <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Blood Loss" href="/Blood+Loss">Blood Loss</a> buildup per hit than the weapon's melee strikes.</li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;<img title="Sell Value" src="/file/Elden-Ring/item_value_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_18px.png" alt="item value icon elden ring wiki guide 18px" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;100</li> 
 <li>Causes&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Hemorrhage" href="/Hemorrhage">Blood Loss</a>&nbsp;Buildup. Base bleed build up is 51 at all weapon upgrade levels.</li> 
 <li>The <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Arcane" href="/Arcane">Arcane</a> scaling of this weapon affects the amount of <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Blood Loss" href="/Blood+Loss">Blood Loss</a> buildup the weapon has.</li> 
 <li>Whilst <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Bloody Finger Nerijus" href="/Bloody+Finger+Nerijus">Nerijus</a> powerstances two of these, it is neither a paired weapon nor possible to obtain two within the same NG cycle without trading with another player.</li> 
 <li>Other notes and player tips go here</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Moveset &amp; Videos in Elden Ring for Reduvia</h3> 
<p><img title="" src="/file/Elden-Ring/reduvia_wep_art.gif" alt="reduvia wep art" width="572" height="315"></p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Videos for the Reduvia Coming Soon</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Reduvia Upgrades in Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>Please see the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Upgrades" href="/Upgrades" target="">Upgrades</a>&nbsp;page to understand the weapon bolstering process.</p> 
<p>Requires regular reinforcement with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones</a></p> 
