				<li id="16537995" class="cmnt-root" data="35" data-d="1647686440000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t576344/Reduvia" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">19 Mar 2022 06:40</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16537995" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">As it seems to have happened with many weapons, their base bleed moght have been lowered to a new base, in Reduvia&apos;s case 50, but raising your Arcane stat starts increasing the bleed buildup. A meager 25 Arcane sets it at 54 bleed buildup, while equipping the Silver Tear Mask (+8 Arcane) raised my Arcane to 33 and my bleed build up to 67. A further 3 points from Marika Scarseal raises the bleed build up yet again to 71, at 36 Arcane. Which also means we can now numerically see how much Arcane is affecting the bleed build up. Time to start focusing more into Arcane. <br/>On a side note, it&apos;s a shame I don&apos;t see any difference in Scorpion Stinger&apos;s Rot build up with Arcane, it SHOULD be an Arcane scaling weapon as well.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16537995" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16537995" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">2</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><sect